      "body" : "@averasko When you use <code>Object.equals(Object)</code> there is no compile time type check. The <code>Objects.equals(Object, Object)</code> works very much the same as a  normal <code>equals</code>, and re inference/checks by IDE, those rules are heuristics that are also supported for <code>Objects.equals(Object, Object)</code> (eg IntelliJ IDEA 2016.2 has the same check for both the normal equals and the one from Objects)."
