  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/11271554/compare-two-objects-in-java-with-possible-null-values",
  "title" : "Compare two objects in Java with possible null values",
  "body" : "<p>I want to compare two strings for equality when either or both can be <code>null</code>.</p>\n<p>So, I can't simply call <code>.equals()</code> as it can contain <code>null</code> values.</p>\n<p>The code I have tried so far :</p>\n<pre><code>boolean compare(String str1, String str2) {\n  return ((str1 == str2) || (str1 != null &amp;&amp; str1.equals(str2)));\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>What will be the best way to check for all possible values including <code>null</code> ?</p>\n"
}